# Modern Simplicity Guide

## The New LAMP Stack

### Modern Components
- **L**: Linux (via Nix) - The new normalize.css for environments
- **A**: ASGI (Uvicorn) - Future-proofed async server
- **M**: MiniDataAPI - Universal SQL simplifier
- **P**: Python + FastHTML/HTMX - The new Webmaster stack

### Why This Matters
- Return to one-person-can-do-it-all development
- Modern tools with simple interfaces
- Future-proofed by design
- No framework fatigue
- Maximum productivity

## Core Principles

### 1. Environment Management
- Nix for reproducible environments
- No more "works on my machine"
- Simple deployment
- Cross-platform compatibility
- Future-proof package management

### 2. Web Development
- FastHTML for Python-based HTML generation
- HTMX for dynamic updates
- No complex JavaScript frameworks
- Server-side rendering
- Simple, observable state

### 3. Data Management
- SQLite as the universal database
- MiniDataAPI for simple data access
- Python dict-like interfaces
- Future-proof data patterns
- Easy to understand and maintain

### 4. Local-First Approach
- Desktop application model
- Full access to local resources
- No complex client/server
- Simple deployment
- Maximum performance

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

### Enterprise Complexity
- Microservices
- Complex ORMs
- Heavy JavaScript frameworks
- Distributed systems
- Over-engineered security

### Framework Fatigue
- JavaScript framework churn
- Complex build systems
- Heavy abstractions
- Unnecessary complexity
- Over-automation

## Best Practices

### Development Workflow
- Use Nix for environments
- Keep it simple
- Stay close to core tools
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions
- Focus on productivity

### Code Organization
- Clear, simple structure
- Minimal dependencies
- Observable behavior
- Easy to understand
- Easy to modify

### Testing Approach
- Simple, pragmatic tests
- Focus on functionality
- Observable behavior
- No complex frameworks
- Easy to maintain

